                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.1100 K77/95.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">President of Nicaragua</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 12, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am greatly gratified at your kind message of the 7th and to learn of the marked
                    courtesies and warm welcome so freely extended to Secretary Knox by Your
                    Excellency’s Government and the people of Nicaragua. Pray accept the expression
                    of my appreciation and my good wishes for your personal prosperity and that of
                    the Nicaraguan people.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Taft.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
